universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant BaldEagle : obj
constant Cow : obj
constant Rabbit : obj
constant Squirrel : obj

constant Chases : obj → obj → Prop
constant Kind : obj → Prop
constant Rough : obj → Prop
constant Needs : obj → obj → Prop
constant Cold : obj → Prop
constant Green : obj → Prop
constant Red : obj → Prop
constant Eats : obj → obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Chases BaldEagle Cow
axiom T2 : Kind BaldEagle
axiom T3 : Rough BaldEagle
axiom T4 : Needs BaldEagle Rabbit
axiom T5 : Chases Cow Rabbit
axiom T6 : Cold Cow
axiom T7 : Green Cow
axiom T8 : Red Cow
axiom T9 : ¬ Chases Rabbit BaldEagle
axiom T10 : Chases Rabbit Cow
axiom T11 : ¬ Eats Rabbit BaldEagle
axiom T12 : Eats Rabbit Cow
axiom T13 : Cold Rabbit
axiom T14 : Green Rabbit
axiom T15 : Eats Squirrel Cow
axiom T16 : ¬ Eats Squirrel Rabbit

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Needs x BaldEagle → Chases BaldEagle Rabbit
axiom R2 : Rough Squirrel ∧ ¬ Kind Squirrel → Green Squirrel
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Chases x BaldEagle → Needs x Squirrel
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Needs x Rabbit → Chases x BaldEagle
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Chases x Cow → Eats Cow BaldEagle
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Chases x BaldEagle ∧ ¬ Needs x BaldEagle → Red x
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Needs x Squirrel → Needs Squirrel Rabbit

theorem squirrel_needs_squirrel : Needs Squirrel Squirrel :=
begin
  apply R7,
  apply R3,
  apply R4,
  exact T4,
end

-- The answer is True

theorem not_squirrel_needs_squirrel : ¬ Needs Squirrel Squirrel :=
